data.title: Alfonso XIII, King of Spain (1886
data.meta_description: This painting by military portraitist José Cusachs y Cusachs shows Alfonso XIII, King of Spain at the age of twenty one. King from birth, he later married Victoria Eugenie of Battenberg, the granddaughter of Queen Victoria. José Cusachs y Cusachs began his career as an officer in the Spanish artillery, taking part in action at Montejurra and Estella. He left the military in 1882 in order to dedicate himself to painting.
